CatDescriptText: Mrs. Dora Nesbit, 122 Trent Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 24, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "Do you approve of women bartenders?" answer reads: "No I don't approve of women attending bars, and the reason is that it's a man's job."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Dora Nesbit, wearing eyeglasses, hoop earrings, and light colored plaid coat with three quarter sleeves, holding handbag in left hand, standing on Liberty Avenue with pedestrians, automobiles, and May Building in background with sign reading "Drugs," Downtown
